Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.05,0:00:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.62,0:00:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my friend and cohost, Izak Marais.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Izak, what’s in store\Nfor this month’s program?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.50,0:00:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lösch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This month we’ll examine the many ways
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.44,0:00:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah assures us that he is with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our music video for this month shows how,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.41,0:00:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from the moment\Nthat we start to take steps
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,toward dedication and baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.28,0:00:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah draws close to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is also with us in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.99,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In this report, we’ll see how he blessed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.52,0:00:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a special preaching effort in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.30,0:00:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is with us\Nas we meet challenges of daily life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as our Sister Reeta and her children learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.91,0:00:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.91,0:01:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the November 2019 edition\Nof JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions have benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.87,0:01:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from the animated series
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.50,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Become Jehovah’s Friend{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other Bible-based videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you enjoyed\Ngetting to know Caleb and Sophia?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.18,0:01:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’ve watched a video,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.18,0:01:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps you’ve wondered:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.18,0:01:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How does the Governing Body know\Nthat the video will turn out exactly right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they see and hear\Nthe video before it exists?’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go behind the scenes\Nand see how this works.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.47,0:01:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Animated videos,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.47,0:02:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like those in the series\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Become Jehovah’s Friend,{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have been helping young ones\Ndraw closer to their heavenly Father
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for several years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.14,0:02:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Mom, I’m rejoicing in the hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.91,0:02:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wee!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you know
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.39,0:02:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that what you see on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.76,0:02:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,might last just a few short minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.23,0:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but it may involve weeks of work
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by a virtual army of volunteers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.27,0:02:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,With so much time and expense\Ninvolved in making an animated video,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of careful planning\Nis required to avoid waste
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and to keep\Nthe process running smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.55,0:02:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take a look at how the effective use
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.45,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of preproduction tools\Nhelp all of these brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.42,0:02:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,work together to take a video
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.55,0:02:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from initial concept to final production.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.79,0:02:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the direction of the Teaching Committee\Nof the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the work begins\Nlong before the artists even get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They provide direction\Non the theme that needs to be taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.07,0:03:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Members of the animation team collaborate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.71,0:03:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop the featured characters\Nas well as plot structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and they work closely\Nwith writers and storyboard artists
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.62,0:03:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop the approved idea\Ninto a story line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.95,0:03:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a complete script is ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole team\Ngathers together for a table read.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.29,0:03:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time the team\Nhears the whole script being read aloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.30,0:03:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dialogue is meant to be heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.33,0:03:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we read it aloud at the table read,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.30,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we pick up on things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn’t see in the written script.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re able to tighten the story
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it as clear as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The script is reviewed\Nby the research team for accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.25,0:03:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it’s revised, polished, and submitted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.35,0:03:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Teaching Committee for approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.52,0:03:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With an approved script in hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:03:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the director then works with an artist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.69,0:04:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to start turning words into pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.29,0:04:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—visualizing each scene on a storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.00,0:04:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,First come the rough boards,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,showing what will be included in each shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the animation world, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,everything you see on screen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be designed and created
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.04,0:04:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—the characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the furniture,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the props, the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.71,0:04:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are all created by a designer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The storyboard really helps us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.98,0:04:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,figure out exactly what we need to create
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’re not creating\Ntoo much or too little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Once approved by the director,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.56,0:04:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the storyboard artist\Ncleans up each of the boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.70,0:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Preliminary recordings of dialogue, music,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and sound effects are added.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.37,0:04:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These are then used by the director
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and compositor to create an animatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.05,0:05:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,An animatic\Nis a rough draft of the entire video.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The animatic is very important for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That way the director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and, more importantly, the Teaching Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.86,0:05:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can see the entire video\Nbefore we are actually making it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.86,0:05:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that they can review it\Nand give us the proper direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The finished animatic is submitted
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Teaching Committee for review.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on direction from the committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the team makes sure\Nthat the teaching points come across clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the finished product\Nis true to the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and intent\Nof the approved concept for the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, using the approved\Nanimatic as a blueprint,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,full production begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, everything in animation\Ncan be very time-consuming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.93,0:05:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,An animator working full-time here at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,may be able to produce\Nfour to six seconds of animation in one week,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and that doesn’t even include other aspects
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.21,0:06:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that are very important, such as modeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.45,0:06:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,rigging, lighting,\Ncompositing, and many others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.62,0:06:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,From the examples shown here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.49,0:06:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see\Njust how closely the final version
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.99,0:06:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the video {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Make Jehovah Happy{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}\Nfollows the animatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Preproduction tools\Nsuch as storyboards and animatics
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,do more than save\Nthe organization time and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.30,0:06:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They enable the Teaching Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.94,0:06:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to carefully evaluate\Nevery project along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the initial approved concept
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the final product
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to keep providing videos
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that help all of us\Nhonor our Friend, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.36,0:06:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it amazing to see all the work
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes into our videos?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.37,0:06:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah provides for his people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.53,0:07:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,just what they need at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, he is with his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.01,0:07:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lösch,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you have some thoughts on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.05,0:07:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about a very common expression
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.19,0:07:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression is:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.89,0:07:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirteen times it’s attributed\Nto a statement from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Three times it’s something that Jesus said
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to one or more of his disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there are dozens of other times
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that the same sentiment\Nis expressed using similar wording.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.24,0:07:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Few things in the world\Nequal the joy humans experience
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,than the birth of a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As children grow up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they are sometimes exposed to situations
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that tend to cause nervousness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:07:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or even fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:08:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So a parent may occasionally feel compelled
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.80,0:08:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to reassure a child:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.80,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have no fear; I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves his servants\Nas if they were his children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, at John 13:1,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.75,0:08:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ feelings for his disciples\Nare well expressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.65,0:08:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus, having loved his own\Nwho were in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,loved them to the end.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we face fears,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.76,0:08:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,trials, or causes for anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.83,0:08:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,both our heavenly Father and his Son, Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reassuringly say, “I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the righteous man Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 6:9 says
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that “Noah walked with the true God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt that Jehovah was with Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He preserved him\Nand his family through the Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.89,0:09:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterward,\NJehovah further proved he was with Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In Genesis chapter 9, Jehovah said:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I am now establishing my covenant with you:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Never again will all flesh be destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.87,0:09:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by the waters of a flood.’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.47,0:09:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah could have made that determination
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and promised himself\Nthat he wouldn’t do that again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.48,0:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead, he reached out to Noah
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and reassured him that he was with him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.45,0:09:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by making the rainbow covenant\Nwith Noah and his offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.86,0:09:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Using similar terminology,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.50,0:09:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah indicated\Nthat he was with Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.67,0:09:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaac, Jacob, Joseph,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.73,0:09:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses, Joshua, and Gideon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.10,0:09:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all individuals\Nwhom Jehovah was pleased with,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so he reassured them that he was with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:10:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How about for a group of people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Jehovah moved to feel the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.09,0:10:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,toward a large crowd\Nof his servants collectively?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.16,0:10:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please find with me Exodus 6:6, 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.73,0:10:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole nation of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.10,0:10:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was experiencing severe trials
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffering as slaves in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Jehovah’s reassurance\Nto the vast number of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.65,0:10:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Verses 6 and 7 state:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.42,0:10:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, say to the Israelites:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.35,0:10:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I am Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.36,0:10:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and I will bring you out\Nfrom under the burdens of the Egyptians
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.29,0:10:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and rescue you from their slavery,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and I will reclaim you\Nwith an outstretched arm
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.13,0:10:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and with great judgments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.20,0:10:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And I will take you in as my people,\Nand I will be your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.64,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you will certainly know\Nthat I am Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.51,0:11:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who is bringing you out\Nfrom under the burdens of Egypt.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.55,0:11:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If that great, mixed group of people\Nwould follow his leadings,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.05,0:11:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he said he’d ‘take them in’\Nand he ‘would be their God.’
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He was reassuring them:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will be with you,”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For forty years in the wilderness,\Nhe was with them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—feeding them, providing water for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.00,0:11:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ensuring that their clothes\Nand sandals would not wear out,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,protecting them\Nfrom poisonous snakes, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.98,0:11:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, when entering the land of promise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.98,0:11:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he protected them during enemy warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.69,0:11:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah promised to be with and to support
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the kings of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as they heeded\Nhis commandments and direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.30,0:11:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,King Solomon was told:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah [your] God . . .\Nwill not desert you or abandon you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.41,0:12:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will be with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,King Asa was informed:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is with you\Nas long as you remain with him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.05,0:12:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When faced with overwhelming enemy forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.89,0:12:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,King Jehoshaphat was told:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.16,0:12:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tomorrow go out against them,\Nand Jehovah will be with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.50,0:12:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah also proved to be\Nwith the many prophets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that he sent out in his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one example is Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.04,0:12:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine if you had Jeremiah’s assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.04,0:12:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose you had been directed to deliver
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a scathing denunciation and judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,against wicked kings,\Ncorrupt priests, and false prophets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.32,0:12:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,underqualified?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.32,0:12:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you feel like a little child
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.56,0:13:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,challenging a whole group of evil grown-ups?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Jeremiah felt\Nas he expressed himself
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.87,0:13:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at Jeremiah 1:6:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I said: ‘Alas, O Sovereign Lord Jehovah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know how to speak,\Nfor I am just a boy.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.92,0:13:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What were Jehovah’s reassuring words\Nin reply?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.42,0:13:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 1:8, 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.76,0:13:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do not be afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘because of their appearance,\Nfor “I am with you to save you,”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.73,0:13:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jehovah stretched out his hand\Nand touched my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.30,0:13:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Jehovah said to me: \N‘I have put my words in your mouth.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah put the words\Nthat you were to say “in your mouth,”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you’d no longer feel\Nlike a little child, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.98,0:13:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t think of Jeremiah\Nas being an incredible superman;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.95,0:14:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he was a human like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s of interest that though Jeremiah\Nlived in another time and place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he faced situations similar to those we face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.60,0:14:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We interact with different types of people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in our daily life,\Nat work, and at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them can be intimidating.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And like Jeremiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.61,0:14:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has commissioned us\Nto go to strangers and preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.62,0:14:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We share the good news of the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.92,0:14:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are interested;\Nothers are just plain apathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But at times, we may come\Nacross someone who is angry
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and may even be threatening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.63,0:14:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the time to remember Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.27,0:14:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Though initially timid,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,he courageously faced
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.88,0:14:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the challenge of an intimidating response.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.01,0:15:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he rally to the occasion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.38,0:15:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because Jehovah had reassured him:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.02,0:15:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.32,0:15:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:\N“I have put my words in your mouth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Jehovah do something similar for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Long after Jeremiah\Nand the other faithful ones
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.40,0:15:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who are recorded\Nin the Hebrew Scriptures came and went,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.58,0:15:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has proved to be\Nwith true Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.95,0:15:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,both past and present.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Find with me John chapter 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true he was a perfect man,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but did Jehovah leave him all alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 8:16,\Nwhat did Jesus himself say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“And yet even if I do judge,\Nmy judgment is truthful,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.21,0:16:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“because I am not alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.21,0:16:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Father who sent me is with me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We might be thinking\Nof that intimidating person in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.58,0:16:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you are facing the person\Nwithout a fellow Witness standing beside you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.59,0:16:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are you really all alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.53,0:16:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus knew that at the most stressful
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and emotionally draining time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.63,0:16:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,during his human life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,his disciples would leave him all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But was he really alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read the inspired account
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at John 16:32.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.98,0:16:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, these are Jesus’ own words:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.52,0:16:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! The hour is coming,\Nindeed, it has come,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“when each one of you\Nwill be scattered to his own house
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you will leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I am not alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.66,0:16:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Father is with me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.97,0:17:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was not alone\Nduring his most anxious moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.44,0:17:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you are alone
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.78,0:17:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,standing at the door\Nof an irritated householder,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.05,0:17:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,think again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.11,0:17:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.28,0:17:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have more with you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.35,0:17:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,than if you had your whole congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.52,0:17:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,standing in the person’s front yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.26,0:17:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why did Jesus share
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.93,0:17:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this precious insight with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.03,0:17:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the next verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus explains his reason\Nfor saying what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.41,0:17:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,John 16:33:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have said these things to you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that by means of me you may have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the world you will have tribulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“but take courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.99,0:17:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I have conquered the world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jesus for addressing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.16,0:17:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,our fears and concerns when giving a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of trembling with fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.70,0:18:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he shared his confidence in Jehovah’s support
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.17,0:18:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we “may have peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He acknowledged\Nthat we would face tribulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.74,0:18:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but he said\Nthat we could look at his example
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.81,0:18:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and have courage\Nto deal with the tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.25,0:18:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.25,0:18:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said in verse 32
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was\Nbecause ‘the Father was with him.’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recall that Jehovah told Jeremiah:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have put my words in your mouth?”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can Jehovah do the same for us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are opposed by unbelievers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Christian Greek Scriptures\Nanswer with a resounding yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.78,0:18:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please follow along with the reading
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the book of Mark chapter 13,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.92,0:18:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and please notice\Nthat the setting Jesus describes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the ministry,\Npreaching the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.59,0:19:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’ve had a good morning in service,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.69,0:19:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you take one more door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.53,0:19:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is irate\Nand even calls the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.70,0:19:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What should you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you say when the police arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.11,0:19:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to be overly concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.71,0:19:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because similar to Jeremiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.12,0:19:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will, in effect,\Nput His words in your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.99,0:19:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark 13:10, 11 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.63,0:19:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“Also, in all the nations,\Nthe good news has to be preached first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.63,0:19:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“And when they are taking you\Nto hand you over,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not be anxious beforehand\Nabout what to say;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“but whatever is given you\Nin that hour, say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.34,0:19:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“for you are not the ones speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but the holy spirit is.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,By this, do we mean that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,will miraculously put words\Nin your mouth for you to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.49,0:20:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.49,0:20:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice verse 11 said
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the holy spirit” is the one speaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.53,0:20:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been taught the basis\Nfor your faith from the Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.44,0:20:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know the reason\Nthat you teach the Bible’s message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.88,0:20:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s all stored in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the holy spirit’s role
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.52,0:20:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are in an intimidating situation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when sharing the good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.03,0:20:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He uses his holy spirit\Nto bring to the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,some of those precious gems\Nthat might be buried in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be amazed at what you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when put under pressure by the authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.51,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or even by outright opposers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.32,0:21:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Add to the fact that Jesus is with you\Nin the disciple-making work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s be reminded\Nof this very encouraging thought
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.96,0:21:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 28:19, 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.67,0:21:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was discussing our commission
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach, teach, and make disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does he conclude\Nthe Bible book of Matthew?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.48,0:21:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read Matthew 28:19, 20:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go, therefore, and make disciples\Nof people of all the nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.49,0:21:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“baptizing them in the name of the Father
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“and of the Son and of the holy spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.46,0:21:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“teaching them to observe\Nall the things I have commanded you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.13,0:21:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“And look!\NI am with you all the days
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,until the conclusion\Nof the system of things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that he is with us now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.77,0:22:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are making disciples\Nand teaching people the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.98,0:22:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And he promises\Nhe’ll support us in this important work
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,until the end\Nof this wicked system of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.12,0:22:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As prophesied, during this time\Nof the conclusion of the system,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we are being persecuted\Nin different areas of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.76,0:22:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Scriptures show,\NSatan and his angels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.70,0:22:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,are “misleading the entire inhabited earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.34,0:22:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, Jehovah’s people\Nhave been persecuted in Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.84,0:22:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But will the persecution
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.88,0:22:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,succeed in eliminating
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.25,0:22:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,true worship in that area of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.45,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.35,0:22:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because Jehovah is with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.16,0:22:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He and Jesus promised: “I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.56,0:23:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia did not learn from the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.20,0:23:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It will prove to be the same for them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.70,0:23:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as it was for Nazi Germany under Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.30,0:23:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought his regime
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.44,0:23:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,could eradicate\Ntrue worship and God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.64,0:23:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from areas under their control.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.65,0:23:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But they made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.31,0:23:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While it is true\Nthat they murdered some 2,000 brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.59,0:23:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end, their scheme ended up in failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.72,0:23:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because God was with us, not with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.96,0:23:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“God with us”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.03,0:23:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,—those words have decorated national emblems
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.50,0:23:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and even the uniforms of soldiers of Prussia
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.74,0:23:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Czarist Russian Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,These words were also\Non the belts of German troops
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.41,0:23:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when they marched into Belgium\Nin the year 1914 of our Common Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.42,0:23:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But they had it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.75,0:24:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Sovereign Lord Jehovah\Nwas with us, not with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.76,0:24:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s with all of us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.96,0:24:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be with us during Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.66,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be with us after Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.30,0:24:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be with us at the end\Nof the Thousand Year Reign of Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.84,0:24:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be with mankind\Nat the end of 100,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.84,0:24:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be with humans\Nat the end of 100 million years
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.01,0:24:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the end of 100 million years\Ntimes 100 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will be with mankind {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and so will Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.29,0:24:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They are both on record as saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.69,0:24:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am with you”!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.30,0:24:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Brother Lösch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.00,0:24:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Jehovah is with his people everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.64,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to see examples of this next.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.44,0:24:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,First is the experience\Nof Adam and Nancy Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.91,0:24:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When they came into the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.91,0:25:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they faced bitter opposition\Nfrom their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.32,0:25:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Jehovah was with them\Nduring this stressful time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.12,0:25:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My family are Hungarian Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.53,0:25:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them were killed\Nin concentration camps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.46,0:25:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s something\Nthat the Holocaust took from me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.07,0:25:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—it took the concept of family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.54,0:25:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.37,0:25:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to know why my family was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.04,0:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me really search\Nat a very young age to see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if there was a real religion out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.85,0:25:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a secular thing to be Jewish;
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.69,0:25:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a cultural thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.02,0:25:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A friend of mine came up to me and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.76,0:25:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have to tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.40,0:25:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“I got this book\Nfrom one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.17,0:25:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the most beautiful book\NI have ever read.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.67,0:25:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Oh, I’ll read it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.17,0:26:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it couldn’t have been a week later
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.21,0:26:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that I got a knock on my door, and there were
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.85,0:26:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,two young women at the door\Nwho started to talk to me about the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.42,0:26:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I started having a study\Non a regular basis with Carolyn,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.62,0:26:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoyed it more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.63,0:26:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,One day my father was home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.13,0:26:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He just screamed at them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.73,0:26:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and basically threw them out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.93,0:26:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It just progressed after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.47,0:26:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just no peace at any time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.31,0:26:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot of tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.48,0:26:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just couldn’t understand
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.54,0:26:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,why they weren’t even asking me:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.88,0:26:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, what is it\Nthat you like about this religion?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.12,0:26:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who are these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.28,0:26:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us talk to—”\NNo, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.42,0:26:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very, very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.76,0:26:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after my baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.43,0:26:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother came up to me, and she said:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.76,0:26:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your father and I are going out for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.16,0:26:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You better not be here when we get home.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.43,0:27:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 17 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.40,0:27:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know where I was going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.41,0:27:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what I was going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.44,0:27:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I trusted in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.81,0:27:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I picked up the phone,\Nand I called my Carolyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.75,0:27:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In what seemed like minutes,\Nthere were brothers and sisters at the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.75,0:27:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They were putting my things into this truck\Nand bringing it over to Carolyn’s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.42,0:27:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, “You can live with me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.33,0:27:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I was baptized,\NI would drive back and forth 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.80,0:27:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to school with a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.37,0:27:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Little by little,\NI was telling him what I was learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “You know,\NI want to meet these people. 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.24,0:27:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some questions.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.71,0:27:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I had questions. 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.94,0:27:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked them:\N“Why do we die?, 
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.31,0:27:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we grow old?,”\Nand so forth and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And they went right to the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.01,0:27:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I left the house after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.15,0:27:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “This is the truth!”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.35,0:27:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up in my house,\Ngoing to church every Sunday
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.22,0:27:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was something that you had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.56,0:28:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I became a teenager,\Nthen religion became less in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.20,0:28:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and basketball became more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.83,0:28:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a young man, you’d watch sports
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.53,0:28:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’d see\Nthat sports players made a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.87,0:28:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My teachers would tell my parents:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.90,0:28:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“He’s going to be a good basketball player.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.41,0:28:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.51,0:28:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“He could be worth, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.91,0:28:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,several hundred thousand dollars\Nby the time he graduates.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.81,0:28:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I received over 125 scholarships.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.15,0:28:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you’re talking about a free education
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.48,0:28:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just because you can play basketball.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.05,0:28:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I realized, you know,\Nat an early age that playing 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.52,0:28:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,professional basketball could mean a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.73,0:28:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not only for me but for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.66,0:28:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So as far as God was concerned,\NI had a little interest in God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.40,0:28:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,(like I would ask my mom questions),
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.20,0:28:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn’t until Nancy\Nbrought me to the Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.04,0:28:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that really something just kicked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.04,0:28:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was studying,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.01,0:28:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and my mom was downstairs in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.45,0:28:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard her crying,\Nand I said, “What’s wrong?”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.21,0:28:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, “I know you’re going to become\None of those Jehovah’s Witnesses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.22,0:28:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So realizing in my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.95,0:29:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’m not going to become\Na basketball player
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.02,0:29:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but that I’m going to become\None of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.72,0:29:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because that’s more important
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.73,0:29:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—that affected me many, many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.36,0:29:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When others found out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.57,0:29:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was going to become\None of Jehovah’s Witnesses, 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.57,0:29:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,people shied away.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.14,0:29:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,People try to use you when they think
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.40,0:29:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you can give them something\Nor you’re going to be somebody big.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.97,0:29:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,By going the direction\Nof serving Jehovah completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.98,0:29:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you lost all the worldly people\Nthat you thought were your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.81,0:29:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that was
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.28,0:29:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in one summer that I started\Nthe study with Brother Crespo,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.49,0:29:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and in six months, I was baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.46,0:29:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we decided to get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.33,0:29:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture that says
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.40,0:29:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘even if my own father\Nand my mother would abandon me,’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.67,0:29:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that even ‘Jehovah would take me in,’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.14,0:29:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—it proved to be true in so many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.87,0:29:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you become one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.08,0:29:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re part of a family\Nthat will do anything for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.51,0:29:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had adversity over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.68,0:30:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah never said\Neverything was going to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.52,0:30:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What he says is\Nthat when you face these problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.25,0:30:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you will not face them alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.16,0:30:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah has never let us down\Nwhen it comes to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.73,0:30:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When their families\Nand friends abandoned them,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.56,0:30:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,did you notice how Jehovah\Ncontinued to be with Adam and Nancy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.37,0:30:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Their spiritual family\Nimmediately stepped in to support them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.88,0:30:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciated what Nancy said:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.34,0:30:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jehovah never said\Neverything will be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.21,0:30:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He said that when you face problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.18,0:30:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you will not face them alone.’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.82,0:30:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She and Adam never felt alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.73,0:30:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, we ask Jehovah\Nto be with us when we need something
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.26,0:30:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—a spiritual need or a material need.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.10,0:30:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we’ll see in this next experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.07,0:30:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,even before we know that we have a need,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.47,0:31:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah already knows what we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.65,0:31:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Reeta.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.71,0:31:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My son is Jackson,\Nand my daughter is Sherina.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.45,0:31:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.12,0:31:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been working\Non a tea estate as a tea picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.76,0:31:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I prayed to God very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.93,0:31:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.40,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please help me to learn about the Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.00,0:31:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Within two days,\NJehovah’s Witnesses came
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.24,0:31:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and knocked on my door,\Nand I agreed to study the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.84,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.47,0:31:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I only prayed yesterday,\Nasking God to help me to study the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.51,0:31:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our meetings begin at 4:45 p.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.85,0:31:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but we have to get ready by 12 o’clock
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.02,0:31:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.85,0:31:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we prepare our bags\Non Wednesday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.49,0:31:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I carry two big bags\Non my shoulders
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.43,0:31:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk for three\Nand a half kilometers (2 mi)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.20,0:31:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the meetings on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.54,0:32:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We love seeing our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.21,0:32:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we always\Ngo to the meetings early.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.71,0:32:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been pioneering now\Nfor a year and six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.46,0:32:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no greater happiness\Nthan what comes from pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.36,0:32:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a onetime opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.40,0:32:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we decided that we should\Ngive the best that we can to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.44,0:32:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I am so happy to be serving this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.68,0:32:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I was not paid at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.45,0:32:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t even have a rupee.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.96,0:33:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On that day, my children and I ate well.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.99,0:33:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But after eating,\Nwe were very worried
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.70,0:33:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about what we were going\Nto do the following day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.23,0:33:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that night,\NI said a prayer with the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.91,0:33:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and we read the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.98,0:33:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.31,0:33:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Don’t worry about tomorrow.’
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.35,0:33:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I trusted that somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.45,0:33:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would give us what we needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.02,0:33:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 10:30 at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.92,0:33:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fast asleep, and the phone rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.26,0:33:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually no one calls this late,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.50,0:33:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wondered,\N‘Who could be calling me this late?’
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.50,0:33:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I picked up the phone,\Nand it was a brother on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.97,0:33:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “Sister,\Ngo to your bookshelf
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.15,0:33:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and take the Greatest Man book.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.75,0:34:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he asked me to turn to a page.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.19,0:34:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I turned to that page,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.89,0:34:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there were 10,000 rupees (about $55, U.S.)\Nbetween those pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.46,0:34:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We could not believe our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.56,0:34:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exactly what we needed\Nfor that month’s expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.47,0:34:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A few days earlier,\Nhe and his wife had visited us
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.60,0:34:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and secretly left the money\Nin the book before leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.41,0:34:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thanked Jehovah in prayer with the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.51,0:34:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah already knew exactly what we needed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.08,0:34:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,even before we realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.92,0:34:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, every night I open the doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.09,0:34:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,go outside, and look up at the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.73,0:34:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When I look up, I see many stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.27,0:34:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I daily meditate about his wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.44,0:34:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,his power,\Nwhat amazing things he is able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.55,0:35:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This earth, this universe
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.11,0:35:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—how amazingly well he cares for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.19,0:35:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He takes care of the smallest thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.26,0:35:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I completely rely on Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.93,0:35:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I remember\Nthat Jehovah has the ability
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.86,0:35:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us with his holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.54,0:35:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s such a loving Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.64,0:35:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s always holding our hand tight,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.08,0:35:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can separate us from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.78,0:35:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone tries, they will fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.65,0:35:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s so generous with his love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.66,0:35:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s so affectionate with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.39,0:35:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can take away\Nthe love Jehovah has for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.70,0:35:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice from Reeta’s experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.70,0:35:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is with us in several ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.37,0:36:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Reeta really appreciates\Ncongregation meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.24,0:36:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They love being with their brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.05,0:36:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.75,0:36:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you value the meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.75,0:36:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the encouraging association\Nyou find there?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.32,0:36:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Reeta takes time to meditate\Non the wonders of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.19,0:36:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and she does more than marvel\Nat what she sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.56,0:36:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She notices\Nhow Jehovah’s love and care for her
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.90,0:36:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is evident in all his works.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.27,0:36:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows that Jehovah\Nhas the power to create anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.14,0:36:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants to use his power in her behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.68,0:36:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no surprise that Reeta is keenly aware
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.62,0:36:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s constant support\Nin her pioneer ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.16,0:36:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah proves to be with us in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.43,0:36:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we’re preaching\Nin our local community
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.20,0:36:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or sharing in a special campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.77,0:36:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go to Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.77,0:37:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch a report about a special campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.00,0:37:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As with Reeta’s experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.14,0:37:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,see if you can identify
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.34,0:37:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah was with the many thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.15,0:37:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,who volunteered for this campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.85,0:37:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Central Europe branch territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.52,0:37:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a special campaign was organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.86,0:37:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the School
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.86,0:37:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for Branch Committee Members and Their Wives
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.26,0:37:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,triggered an evaluation of how much territory
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.06,0:37:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the countries we oversee\Nis not really covered thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.07,0:37:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we asked our circuit overseers
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.37,0:37:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to recommend to us which sections 
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.07,0:37:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the congregation’s territory
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.11,0:37:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,could be listed\Nas so-called “unassigned territory.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.81,0:37:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All in all, we received\Nover 11,000 territories
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.75,0:37:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from the congregations,\Nwith approximately 3 million inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.35,0:37:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So because of this grand scale,\Nthere was suddenly the idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.92,0:37:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why not organize\Na special preaching campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.39,0:38:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to cover all these territories
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.86,0:38:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on one single weekend?’
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.57,0:38:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This was really exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.57,0:38:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And after getting\Nthe Branch Committee’s approval,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.90,0:38:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Service Department\Nstarted to organize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.01,0:38:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest, at first,\Nwe were not really sure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.24,0:38:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,how the publishers\Nwould react to such a campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.08,0:38:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But we fully trusted in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.55,0:38:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the response was stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.72,0:38:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 20,000 publishers participated
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.25,0:38:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and were assigned\Nto all these territories throughout Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.22,0:38:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The campaign took place\Non one weekend in May 2017
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.80,0:38:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and was especially successful\Nin metropolitan areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.93,0:38:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as in Berlin, Hamburg, and Düsseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.37,0:38:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,At one door, a man just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.28,0:38:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to open his shop\Nwhere he sells Arabian specialties.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.91,0:38:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We were able to show him a video in Arabic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.15,0:38:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he gave us his address and phone number.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.99,0:39:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He also agreed\Nto have someone visit him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.59,0:39:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it’s really a privilege\Nto join in such a campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.39,0:39:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see that every human\Nis precious to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.13,0:39:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter where they live\Nor where they come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.93,0:39:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the need\Nand the fantastic response in 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.80,0:39:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it was decided to repeat\Nsuch a campaign in May 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.74,0:39:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time it was expanded to Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.48,0:39:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Austria, Luxembourg, and Liechtenstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.78,0:39:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And now imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.62,0:39:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,over 32,000 publishers participated,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.42,0:39:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which is actually over 60 percent more
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.39,0:39:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,than in May 2017.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.83,0:39:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This was really faith-strengthening.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.30,0:39:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, a lot\Nof wonderful experiences were reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.70,0:39:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.70,0:39:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where you are in Berlin,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.80,0:39:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see small groups\Nof brothers everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.31,0:39:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That was really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.31,0:39:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the ministry we met a woman,\Nand she told us 
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.31,0:39:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that she had just prayed for a Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.31,0:40:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We are now more than ever convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.21,0:40:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah leads all this work
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.82,0:40:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,through his angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.85,0:40:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Sunday, we had a nice experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.39,0:40:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman called us from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.39,0:40:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She had actually already passed us,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.03,0:40:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but she had the feeling\Nshe had to go back again
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.93,0:40:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—she told us later.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.27,0:40:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,After she had invited us to her home,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.14,0:40:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we exchanged our contact information
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.41,0:40:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and we also filled in\Nthe online contact form.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.38,0:40:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Had we been in the territory\Njust one minute later,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.28,0:40:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we would never have made the contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.52,0:40:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This must have been guided by the angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.92,0:40:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday morning while in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.92,0:40:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a young man ran after us\Nand asked us what we were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.46,0:40:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We explained it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.13,0:40:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked us why there is still\Nso much evil in the world, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.46,0:40:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the afternoon,\Nwe were able to call on him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.93,0:40:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We could start a Bible study right away
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.07,0:40:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and arrange a return visit,\Nwhich we will make today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.44,0:41:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Being together\Nwith the friends is just so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.61,0:41:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re out and about with a large group.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.81,0:41:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You meet up again regularly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.51,0:41:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to change partners and to relate experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.92,0:41:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.35,0:41:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of videos were shown,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.09,0:41:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot of Bible studies were started.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.79,0:41:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is very interesting\Nis that a lot of publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.56,0:41:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,felt motivated\Nto expand their ministry after the campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.50,0:41:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For sure,\Nthese preaching campaigns truly prove
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.43,0:41:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah and Jesus\Nare directing the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.47,0:41:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the angels are helping us\Nin reaching out to all people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.38,0:41:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we really have a lot of reasons\Nto be Jehovah’s happy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.49,0:41:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah truly proved to be
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.06,0:41:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with all who volunteered\Nto share in this campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.79,0:41:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How else could the good news\Nreach three million people
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.46,0:41:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in such a well-organized way?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.50,0:42:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d like to thank\Nthe more than 32,000 brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.24,0:42:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who shared in this special work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.88,0:42:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As Brother Lösch noted in his talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.88,0:42:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with us in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.05,0:42:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt he is directing\Nthe global preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.59,0:42:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,through Jesus and his angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.29,0:42:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how many people were contacted
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.02,0:42:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,soon after they prayed for a Bible study
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.66,0:42:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or for a question to be answered?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.06,0:42:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.23,0:42:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re together\Nwith a large group of Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.57,0:42:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry\Nand at our meetings and assemblies,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.47,0:42:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we really feel Jehovah’s blessing, don’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.61,0:42:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if we’re isolated?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.98,0:42:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we’re facing persecution?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.78,0:42:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Alphonse Takla\Nexperienced some years ago in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.49,0:42:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see how Jehovah proved to be with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.53,0:43:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All was dark;
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.80,0:43:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,everything was pitch-black dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.80,0:43:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Egypt was at war with Israel,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.04,0:43:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were arresting the brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.34,0:43:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,charging us of practicing illegal activities
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.75,0:43:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as a banned organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.58,0:43:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,On that night, we were being transferred
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.89,0:43:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to the concentration camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.32,0:43:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn’t see much.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.09,0:43:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“What’s going on there?\NWhat’s this place look like? Where is it?”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.94,0:43:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The officer got two soldiers to escort us
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.18,0:43:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to our cell where the brothers were.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.11,0:43:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew that when people\Nare taken to the concentration camp,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.92,0:44:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they spend years
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.09,0:44:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and some of them never return back.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.19,0:44:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was, you know, a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.19,0:44:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked the characters in the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.36,0:44:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,like Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.67,0:44:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.94,0:44:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.97,0:44:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that they were\Nchampions of true worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.24,0:44:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At some stage, I felt jealous of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.54,0:44:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They had this huge relationship with God,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.05,0:44:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so I’d like to be part of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.15,0:44:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I continued to read the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.32,0:44:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to get closer to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.36,0:44:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that Jehovah would look after me;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.29,0:44:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,he would not abandon his servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.26,0:44:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tried to encourage them:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.30,0:44:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Brothers, keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.37,0:44:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re here because we worship Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.34,0:44:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We sat together to discuss, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.74,0:44:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what we were going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.17,0:44:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep spiritually strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.31,0:44:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So we thought that we needed to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.68,0:45:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We picked out a scripture every day,\Nlike a daily text,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.82,0:45:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then after that, recited scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.65,0:45:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One would handle\Na talk from the memory of heart
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.56,0:45:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and then an open discussion \Nof Bible questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.86,0:45:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At that stage,\Nwe didn’t have a Bible with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.54,0:45:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The officers wanted us to renounce our faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.01,0:45:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so they told me to lay on the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.31,0:45:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and there they started to beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.65,0:45:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole camp was around,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.65,0:45:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the prisoners fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.12,0:45:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to pray to Jehovah:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.39,0:45:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah, help me to be able to endure that!”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.32,0:45:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very severe pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.33,0:45:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt his help\Nbecause after a few beatings,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.26,0:45:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,my body felt numb.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.26,0:45:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t feel much more pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.60,0:45:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the prisoners said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.97,0:45:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“If I get out of here alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:46:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’ll tell my children\Nthat in the concentration camp,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.14,0:46:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“I saw the Christians that reminded me\N of the first-century Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.18,0:46:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—that they were happy even to die\Nwithout renouncing their faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.65,0:46:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the officers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.66,0:46:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—this nasty one\Nthat used to beat us very, very severely—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.06,0:46:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,came one day and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.40,0:46:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“We need two of you to come out
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.53,0:46:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and write a report about what you believe.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.33,0:46:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we thought about it:\N‘Is it wise to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.37,0:46:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe they will use it against us.’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.37,0:46:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we prayed to Jehovah\Nfor help to make a decision here,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.68,0:46:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to guide us on what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.85,0:46:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the end, we reached a point that,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.01,0:46:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we may get out; we may not.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.38,0:46:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So we might as well give them a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.02,0:46:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I told the officer, “We need a Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.39,0:46:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, “What for?”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.96,0:46:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to him, “Because we need\Nto quote from the Bible in this report.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.60,0:47:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he said,\N“OK, do you have a Bible in the storeroom?”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.44,0:47:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Yes, I have a Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.07,0:47:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “OK, go and get your Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.31,0:47:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to my bag and picked up the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.19,0:47:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So he picked up the Bible from my hand,\Nopened it randomly, and started to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.79,0:47:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Numbers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.00,0:47:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at me.\N“Who wrote this book?”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.43,0:47:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to him, “Moses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.00,0:47:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’re a liar!” at the top of his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.70,0:47:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I kept quiet,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.74,0:47:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and he closed the book again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.68,0:47:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and opened it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.28,0:47:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’re a liar!”\Nagain at the top of his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.59,0:47:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was racing in my mind\Nwhere it is written in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.79,0:48:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah told Moses to write any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.36,0:48:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He shut the book again,\Nand for a third time,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.00,0:48:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,opened it again,\Nand he started to read in a loud voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.31,0:48:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the officer looked at me\Nwith a big surprise on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.28,0:48:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After we wrote the report,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.15,0:48:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him,\N“Can we keep the Bible, please?”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.85,0:48:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “OK, keep the Bible.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.42,0:48:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,For three months, nearly every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.99,0:48:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the officers came in and beat us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.70,0:48:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and expected us to compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.73,0:48:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We never did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.10,0:48:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can say is that it was Jehovah’s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.67,0:48:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was helping us to endure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.74,0:48:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—to continue to do his will
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.01,0:48:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by not compromising\Nbecause we belong to him
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.88,0:48:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we rely on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.58,0:49:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,God will not abandon his servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.82,0:49:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was Alphonse thrown into prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.96,0:49:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t because he refused to say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.06,0:49:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a simple greeting\Nto the president of his country.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.43,0:49:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that phrase was a political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.80,0:49:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Like many Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.27,0:49:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Alphonse was persecuted for his neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.41,0:49:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped Alphonse to be loyal?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.18,0:49:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.81,0:49:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He prayed to maintain\Na strong spiritual routine,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.98,0:49:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he prayed when he had to make a decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.85,0:49:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and he prayed for help\Nto endure brutal treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.09,0:49:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Alphonse,\Ndo you depend on the power of prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.36,0:49:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Alphonse and, earlier, Reeta
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.63,0:49:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,likened their relationship\Nwith Jehovah to holding His hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.64,0:49:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Reeta said,\N‘Jehovah holds our hand tight.’
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.44,0:49:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alphonse said, “All I can say\Nis that it was Jehovah’s hand.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.45,0:50:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful image!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.02,0:50:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how close we can be to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.89,0:50:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s music video reminds us of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.29,0:50:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is always willing to hold our hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.33,0:50:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s entitled {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Jehovah’s Always by Our Side.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.08,0:50:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, I felt scared inside,\NOnly looking for a place to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.86,0:50:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The world made me feel different. \NNow I hold my head up high.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.20,0:50:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he’d be my confidence,\NThat he’d come to my defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.10,0:51:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,His love I can’t deny,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.17,0:51:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,’Cause he gave me\NCourage when I was feeling weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.11,0:51:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage when I could not speak,\NCourage in my darkest night,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.16,0:51:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to stand up tall,\NCourage to face it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.16,0:51:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to trust him with my life.\NJehovah’s always by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.30,0:51:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He walks with me\NTo help me see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.08,0:51:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His ways are always right.\NHe’ll take my hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.05,0:51:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me understand\NIt’s worth the sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.27,0:52:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not alone.\NEven far away from home,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.87,0:52:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be your guide.\NHe will pick you up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.78,0:52:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you think you’ve had enough\NAnd make you strong and wise,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.63,0:52:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,’Cause he’ll give you\NCourage when you are feeling weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.23,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage when you cannot speak,\NCourage in your darkest nights,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to stand up tall,\NCourage to face it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.78,0:52:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to trust him with your life.\NJehovah’s always by our side—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.76,0:53:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Always, always.\NJehovah’s always by our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.27,0:53:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He walks with you and me\NTo help us see
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.91,0:53:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His ways are always right.\NJehovah’s always by our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.12,0:53:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll take our hand,\NHelp us understand
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.82,0:53:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s worth the sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.16,0:53:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me\NCourage when I was feeling weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.17,0:53:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage when I could not speak,\NCourage in my darkest night,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.98,0:53:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to stand up tall,\NCourage to face it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.52,0:54:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage to trust him with my life.\NJehovah’s always by our side—
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.23,0:54:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Always, always.\NJehovah’s always by our side—
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.21,0:54:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Always, always.\NJehovah’s always by our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.19,0:54:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful song!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.43,0:54:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For many months on JW Broadcasting,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.80,0:54:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve enjoyed a series\Nof video dramatizations
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.64,0:54:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about applying Bible principles in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.47,0:54:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have learned\Nthat we can enjoy happier lives today
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.08,0:55:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and live in a way that pleases God
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.75,0:55:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when we apply\NJehovah’s principles and standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.88,0:55:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Applying God’s principles\Nalso gives us a wonderful hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.72,0:55:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As our concluding video in this series shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.59,0:55:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing on our future hope
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.76,0:55:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to build the faith
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.77,0:55:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to withstand trials we face today.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.80,0:55:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See if you remember these scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.95,0:55:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting baptized
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.08,0:55:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was the most important decision I ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.42,0:55:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it took some time to realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.62,0:55:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that was just the start of my Christian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.62,0:55:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it was hard to show courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.93,0:55:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you people get involved\Nand make a real difference for once?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.44,0:55:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was hard for my son too.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.47,0:56:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.47,0:56:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a Jehovah’s Witness,\Nand I don’t celebrate birthdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.48,0:56:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What? 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.24,0:56:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hum?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.05,0:56:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.91,0:56:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, sign it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.75,0:56:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I really liked Lucas,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.21,0:56:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was very sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.28,0:56:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to sign his birthday card,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.36,0:56:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but Dad helped me to see\Nhow Jehovah felt about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.53,0:56:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that helped me be brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.56,0:56:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I still didn’t sign the card,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.23,0:56:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’m going to do something else for Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.48,0:56:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents had always set\Na good example for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.48,0:56:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But after I moved\Nto serve where the need was greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.85,0:56:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed like my parents were growing apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.02,0:56:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you both doing OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.39,0:56:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don’t look OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.39,0:56:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we’re OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.93,0:56:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,OK? We’re doing wonderful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.53,0:56:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we’re doing good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.53,0:56:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.10,0:56:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.13,0:57:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, they told me that what helped them
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.53,0:57:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,was their love for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.60,0:57:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They meditated on the example\Nof Abraham and Sarah,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.34,0:57:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who showed honor to each other\Nby listening and by caring.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.75,0:57:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That example really helped my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.55,0:57:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.05,0:57:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve seen how it can help\Nin any relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.56,0:57:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a long way from home,\Nbut showing love to others
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.09,0:57:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—it helps me to stay happy in my assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.17,0:57:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When our doctor told us that our baby
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.40,0:57:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,would likely be born with severe problems
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.47,0:57:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and could even die,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.94,0:57:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it was more than I could bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.05,0:57:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And because my husband\Nwas not one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.39,0:57:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed God’s help more than ever
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.29,0:58:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to calm my heart and help me explain\Nwhy I could never have an abortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.96,0:58:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though it took me years
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.03,0:58:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,before I would agree to a Bible study
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.80,0:58:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and even more years before I made\Nenough changes to qualify for baptism,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.41,0:58:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the life we have now
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.88,0:58:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,—serving Jehovah together—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.95,0:58:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing could make me happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.78,0:58:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing could make us happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.79,0:58:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness really does come\Nfrom serving Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.16,0:58:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but serving him faithfully\Ndefinitely takes courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.40,0:58:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so hard for me\Nto turn down that girl at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.30,0:58:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt so guilty\Nfor how involved I’d gotten with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.34,0:58:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle used the Bible\Nto help me get back on track
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.38,0:58:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and to remind me\Nof two other very important things:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.68,0:58:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was proud of me\Nand that I was not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.35,0:59:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,James 1:2, 3 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.16,0:59:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Consider it all joy, my brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.83,0:59:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“when you meet with various trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.83,0:59:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“knowing as you do
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.86,0:59:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“that this tested quality of your faith
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.23,0:59:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,produces endurance.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.04,0:59:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think about that scripture a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.07,0:59:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because soon I’ll probably be sent
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.74,0:59:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to prison for refusing military service.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.88,0:59:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Being courageous with that classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.88,0:59:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me build the faith\Nand courage that I need now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.55,0:59:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can give up anything for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.65,0:59:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I might live in a small cell for now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.06,0:59:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but in Paradise,\NI’m going to travel everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.53,0:59:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I get lonely, but that’s OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.57,0:59:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a choice that I’ve made\Nto stay in my assignment right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.60,0:59:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the future, if I choose to get married,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.91,0:59:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope to have a marriage like my parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.05,1:00:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hope that Lucas is resurrected\Nso I can show him around Paradise
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.08,1:00:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and teach him more about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.65,1:00:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I showed him pictures,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.86,1:00:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but the real thing will be so much better.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.79,1:00:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I can hold my baby girl again.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.20,1:00:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Our program \Nhas focused on the many ways
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.70,1:00:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.31,1:00:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s with us\Nas we work toward dedication
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.31,1:00:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and baptism.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.35,1:00:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s with us at our congregation meetings
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.62,1:00:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we are with our spiritual family.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.15,1:00:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s with us as we successfully face
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.36,1:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,persecution and hardship.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.59,1:00:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is with us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.59,1:00:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when we share the good news of his Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.50,1:00:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with everyone we meet.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.20,1:00:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And, Brother Marais,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.30,1:00:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate that you were here with me
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.21,1:01:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for this month’s program.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.21,1:01:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Lösch.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.31,1:01:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We end this month’s program
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.48,1:01:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with a visit to our brothers\Nand sisters in Tenerife.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.12,1:01:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenerife is the largest\Nof the Canary Islands,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.92,1:01:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,an archipelago\Noff the northwest coast of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.69,1:01:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These islands\Nwere formed by volcanic eruptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.89,1:01:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest point
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.96,1:01:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is the dormant Teide volcano on Tenerife.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.27,1:01:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the weather\Nis mild and sunny throughout the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.34,1:01:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This has made the Canary Islands famous\Nfor their extensive banana plantations.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.35,1:01:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenerife is a popular tourist destination.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.39,1:01:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s home to nearly a million people,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.42,1:01:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but more than ten million visitors
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.46,1:01:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,come every year to enjoy the beaches,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.40,1:01:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the lush terrain,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.70,1:02:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and the food.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.77,1:02:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The island of Tenerife has 33 congregations
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.77,1:02:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and more than 3,000 publishers,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.08,1:02:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,492 of whom are regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.88,1:02:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the influx of visitors\Nfrom all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.89,1:02:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters\Npreach in over 15 languages,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.92,1:02:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,including Russian,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.46,1:02:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,German,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.30,1:02:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,French,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.77,1:02:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hindi,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.13,1:02:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and Romanian.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.37,1:02:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They preach everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.04,1:02:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—in the cities\Nas well as the rural and mountainous regions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.65,1:02:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters in Tenerife
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.65,1:02:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,send you\Ntheir warm Christian love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.56,1:02:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.26,1:03:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
